ets (P < 0.01). It was concluded that +SBV and-SBV piglets do not differ in their response to the backtest, and only subtle differences were found in their response to novelty. More research is warranted to identify the traits underlying SBV for growth in pigs. Moreover, castrated male piglets seemed to react more fearfully to each test than female piglets. © 2013 American Society of Animal Science. All rights reserved.},
